{"schema": {"fields":[{"type":"integer","name":"index"},{"type":"string","name":"author_association"},{"type":"string","name":"body"},{"type":"datetime","name":"created_at"},{"type":"string","name":"html_url"},{"type":"integer","name":"id"},{"type":"string","name":"issue_url"},{"type":"string","name":"node_id"},{"type":"datetime","name":"updated_at"},{"type":"string","name":"url"},{"type":"string","name":"user"}],"pandas_version":"0.20.0","primaryKey":["index"]}, "data": [{"index":0,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":"\/ping @Julien-Arlandis\r\n\/ping @Ben-Mack\r\n\r\nUsage:\r\n```javascript\r\nmaterial.normalMapType = THREE.ObjectSpaceNormalMap; \/\/ default: THREE.TangentSpaceNormalMap\r\n```\r\n\r\n@bhouston nomenclature can be changed later.\r\n\r\nAn example can also be added later if desired. This PR is backwards-compatible.\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2018-06-08T04:45:27.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14239#issuecomment-395645467","id":395645467,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14239","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5NTY0NTQ2Nw==","updated_at":"2018-06-08T04:45:27.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/395645467","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":1,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Would you consider not moving this into the core, as the object space normal map might be used disproportionately less compared to tangent space maps? This can be solved on top of the library.\r\n\r\nThe most recent material extension thread is this #14232.\r\n\r\nWhat i'm suggesting:\r\n\r\n99% percent of the users, for many years:\r\n\r\n```\r\n\/\/no extra code, smaller library \r\nmyMaterial.normalMap = myTangentNormalMap\r\n```\r\n\r\n1% of the users, recent request\r\n```\r\nvar utils = require('three-material-utils') \/\/user downloads extra code, bigger library\r\n\r\nutils.objectNormalMap(myMaterial) \/\/it's optional, not part of the core for 99% of the users\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nRelated: \r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14245\r\n^why are you extending `THREE.ShaderChunk` if they are being deprecated. The pattern applied to other PRs would block this because of `NodeMaterial`?\r\n\r\nhttps:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7522\r\n^why are you writing GLSL if it's not future proof, this looks like a job for `Node`?\r\n\r\nI would like to ask for this to be postponed and possibly done with `onBeforeCompile` which i would be more than happy to do tomorrow. \r\n\r\nIt adds too much code to the core, for an API that's being deprecated, further coupling built-in materials with the core. ","created_at":"2018-06-08T20:31:17.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14239#issuecomment-395881730","id":395881730,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14239","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5NTg4MTczMA==","updated_at":"2018-06-08T20:40:53.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/395881730","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/4681282?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/pailhead","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ2ODEyODI=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"pailhead","type":"User","id":4681282,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/orgs"}},{"index":2,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Code illustration for this problem:\r\n\r\n`my_normal_fragment_maps.glsl`\r\n```glsl \r\nnormal = texture2D( normalMap, vUv ).xyz * 2.0 - 1.0; \r\n\r\n#ifdef FLIP_SIDED\r\n  normal = - normal;\r\n#endif\r\n\r\n#ifdef DOUBLE_SIDED\r\n  normal = normal * ( float( gl_FrontFacing ) * 2.0 - 1.0 );\r\n#endif\r\n\r\nnormal = normalize( object_space_normal_normalMatrix * normal );\r\n```\r\n\r\n(removes the need for `#ifdef` branching, since you only inject this when you know you'll be using these type of normal maps)\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n\r\nvar myMaterial = new Material()\r\n\r\nmyMaterial.onBeforeCompile = shader =>{ \r\n  shader.uniforms.object_space_normal_normalMatrix = { value: myObject.normalMatrix } \r\n  shader.fragmentShader = 'uniform mat3 object_space_normal_normalMatrix;\\n' + shader.fragmentShader.replace('#include <normal_fragment_maps>', require('my_normal_fragment_maps.glsl') }\r\n```\r\n\r\nI read this as three lines of JS, and some data stored as a string. This PR touches 13 files, for what may end up being dead code for most people. If all the apps in existence got updated to the version of three.js that has this, this would be guaranteed dead code in all of those apps.\r\n","created_at":"2018-06-08T20:52:14.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14239#issuecomment-395886830","id":395886830,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14239","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5NTg4NjgzMA==","updated_at":"2018-06-09T04:25:29.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/395886830","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/4681282?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/pailhead","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ2ODEyODI=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"pailhead","type":"User","id":4681282,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/orgs"}},{"index":3,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"This is a great change @WestLangley.   Thank you.","created_at":"2018-06-09T14:35:25.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14239#issuecomment-395974091","id":395974091,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14239","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5NTk3NDA5MQ==","updated_at":"2018-06-09T14:35:25.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/395974091","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/588541?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/bhouston","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU4ODU0MQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"bhouston","type":"User","id":588541,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/orgs"}},{"index":4,"author_association":"NONE","body":"Very good work\/ Thanks !","created_at":"2018-06-12T12:17:47.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14239#issuecomment-396568673","id":396568673,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14239","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5NjU2ODY3Mw==","updated_at":"2018-06-12T12:17:47.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/396568673","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/7882661?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Julien-Arlandis","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc4ODI2NjE=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Julien-Arlandis","type":"User","id":7882661,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/orgs"}},{"index":5,"author_association":"NONE","body":"3Dmap with the new normal map configuration : http:\/\/vm1.3dmap.fr:1357\/mapRender\/?ref=savoie\r\nHow to know when the commit will be passed on the official lib?","created_at":"2018-06-13T07:37:22.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14239#issuecomment-396843824","id":396843824,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14239","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5Njg0MzgyNA==","updated_at":"2018-06-13T07:37:22.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/396843824","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/7882661?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/Julien-Arlandis","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjc4ODI2NjE=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"Julien-Arlandis","type":"User","id":7882661,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/Julien-Arlandis\/orgs"}},{"index":6,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","body":">How to know when the commit will be passed on the official lib?\r\n\r\nIt may not have been merged because @pailhead has requested it not be.","created_at":"2018-06-14T16:37:17.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14239#issuecomment-397359466","id":397359466,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14239","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5NzM1OTQ2Ng==","updated_at":"2018-06-14T16:37:17.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/397359466","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars2.githubusercontent.com\/u\/1000017?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/WestLangley","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEwMDAwMTc=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"WestLangley","type":"User","id":1000017,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/WestLangley\/orgs"}},{"index":7,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":">It may not have been merged because @pailhead has requested it not be.\r\n\r\nEh, when you put it like this.... :smile: \r\n\r\nI don't want to be the one blocking this, but i do want to start a discussion that may block this (in the current context).\r\n\r\nIssues:\r\n\r\n1. extra code\r\n2. lots of files touched\r\n3. should it be on the material, or on the map? \r\n```javascript\r\nvar myNormalMap = new Texture({normal: THREE.ObjectSpaceNormal})\r\n```\r\n4. is the best way to do this with defines, could it be different chunks for legibility? (don't overload `normalmap_pars_fragment` and `normal_fragment_maps` have the Renderer use the appropriate chunk based on the type of normal map)\r\n\r\n\r\nOn 1 and 2, i'm curious how is this request different from any other request that's asking for something to be done that's not in the examples. On 1 in particular, it's not that much code, but it is extra code. 2 complicates the core, which may not be the best thing to do given the `NodeMaterial` proposal (these i imagine would be two different normal mapping nodes, hence it ties into 4).\r\n\r\nOn 3 and 4  it also ties into this user request, just because someone requested it shouldn't mean that we should just scramble to land this ASAP, i think it needs to be reviewed. \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n","created_at":"2018-06-14T19:57:38.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14239#issuecomment-397419490","id":397419490,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14239","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5NzQxOTQ5MA==","updated_at":"2018-06-14T19:57:38.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/397419490","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/4681282?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/pailhead","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ2ODEyODI=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"pailhead","type":"User","id":4681282,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/orgs"}},{"index":8,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Related:\r\n\r\nThe three.js community has started looking into other engines and tools for integration and influence. I'm not sure if three will be merged with Sea3D, but Unity too was cited as influence for https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/7522.\r\n\r\nIf we are looking at unity for guidance, this is what a texture object looks like in unity:\r\n![unity normal maps](https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/4681282\/41435344-5eec6bf8-6fd3-11e8-8d7f-b9fe298f6dbd.PNG)\r\n![map_type](https:\/\/user-images.githubusercontent.com\/4681282\/41435392-88a20f5c-6fd3-11e8-8b67-11444c243aed.jpg)\r\n\r\nThe material then just takes the texture.\r\n\r\nI don't just putting all this stuff on the `Material` and coupling it with `WebGLRenderer` in so many places. I'd prefer something more generic going on, where the renderer can set this up properly in the most abstract way possible. In the future it could figure out which node to use or switch out, now, it could be a different Chunk. \r\n\r\n\r\nI can't find an option for object\/tangent space, but i'd assume it would belong on the texture.\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\n\r\nvar myTmap = new Texture()\r\nvar myOmap = new Texture()\r\n\r\nvar myMaterial = new Material()\r\n\r\nmyMaterial.normalMap = myTmap\r\nmyMaterial.normalMapType = THREE.TangentSpaceNormalMap \/\/ no bueno, why can't Material just know what kind of map i gave it\r\n\r\n\/\/now i want to change it\r\nmyMaterial.normalMap = myOmap \/\/ myOmap already knows its Object space\r\n\r\n\/\/but i have to inform my Material of this :((((((\r\n\/\/i dont want to do that, the computer can figure this out faster and safer\r\nmyMaterial.normalMapType = THREE.ObjectSpaceNormalMapType \r\n```\r\n","created_at":"2018-06-14T20:07:03.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14239#issuecomment-397422212","id":397422212,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14239","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5NzQyMjIxMg==","updated_at":"2018-06-14T20:11:23.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/397422212","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars0.githubusercontent.com\/u\/4681282?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/pailhead","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjQ2ODEyODI=","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"pailhead","type":"User","id":4681282,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/pailhead\/orgs"}},{"index":9,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"Why is @pailhead capable of blocking perfectly good PRs?","created_at":"2018-06-14T20:12:08.000Z","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/mrdoob\/three.js\/pull\/14239#issuecomment-397423477","id":397423477,"issue_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/14239","node_id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM5NzQyMzQ3Nw==","updated_at":"2018-06-14T20:12:08.000Z","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/repos\/mrdoob\/three.js\/issues\/comments\/397423477","user":{"following_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/following{\/other_user}","events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/events{\/privacy}","avatar_url":"https:\/\/avatars3.githubusercontent.com\/u\/588541?v=4","url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston","gists_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/gists{\/gist_id}","html_url":"https:\/\/github.com\/bhouston","subscriptions_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/subscriptions","node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjU4ODU0MQ==","repos_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/repos","received_events_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/received_events","gravatar_id":"","starred_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/starred{\/owner}{\/repo}","site_admin":false,"login":"bhouston","type":"User","id":588541,"followers_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/followers","organizations_url":"https:\/\/api.github.com\/users\/bhouston\/orgs"}},{"index":10,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","body":"If i know that the texture i'm loading is a normal map, and that it's in object space, i don't want to have to inform every material in the scene (and out of the scene) that it needs to treat that map as such.\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nvar my_shared_OBJECT_SPACE_normal_map = loadTexture()\r\n\r\nscene.traverse( o=>{\r\nif(o.material.normalMap === my_shared_OBJECT_SPACE_normal_map){\r\n  o.material.objectSpaceNormalMap = true\r\n}\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nI'd rather have:\r\n\r\n```javascript\r\nvar my_shared_OBJECT_SPACE_normal_map = loadTexture()\r\nmy_shared_OBJECT_SPACE_normal_map.space = \"object\"\r\n``